From Friday night to Saturday sundown, markets and shops close and public transport interrupts its work.
But Sunday morning begins a new work week.
In many cafes, restaurants and hotels only kosher food is served, which excludes pork, seafood, fish without scales and dishes in which milk and meat are combined.
There is a wide selection of dishes based on beef and lamb, soups and desserts prepared with coconut milk, the traditional Hebrew cream called hummus, a wide variety of salsas, Falafel, which are balls of ground chickpea, fruits and vegetables.
