The diplomats imprisoned were released 444 days after the negotiating intervention of the Algerian government.
In the U.S., his fate caused a wave of solidarity and cheering against Iran.
The failure in Iran contributed decisively to the defeat of Jimmy Carter in front of Ronald Reagan in the 1980 presidential election.
The director and actor Ben Affleck's film "Argo" themes an episode of this story, which sew a little success for America.
Shortly before occupying the embassy, six employees escaped from the building.
After a complicated peril, they ended up in the residence of the Canadian embassy.
CIA, in collaboration with the Canadian authorities, managed to get them out of Iran, to help a covert story an extravagant point: they came out with Canadian passports, as members of the film team examining the location in the country for the shooting of a science fiction superproduction.
Gender combination
