Argo's weakness is the discontrol that arises from the need to show too much action in too many places.
Alan Arkin and John Goodman have a very funny role as Hollywood collaborators, although their characters deserve more space and are not, much less, the only ones in this film.
For these reasons, Affleck's film loses a little dramatic trace, but it is a film that can be followed with a moderate interest, evaluate its realization and the retro style of a thriller that evokes the 1970s.
