However, achieving the annulment of dubious registrations in trademark registration is complicated and also involves a lot of money.
Processes can last for up to nine years and the result is uncertain.
Pattloch talks about cases in which the court dismissed a lawsuit because it had been so long since the name in question had already become a "market reality".
"If the plaintiff is in bad luck, he may even have to pay money to the plagiarist because the process has damaged his brand in China," says Pattloch.
Sometimes this is the law of the jungle.
Some of the best known cases have to do with graphic elements.
