After tearing off large sulphur rocks, which in total weigh about 70 kilos, carry them in two bamboo baskets that carry over their shoulders through steep stone paths.
It is only 250 meters up to the top of the volcano, which rises to 2,386 meters of altitude, but the exhausted carriers take more than 40 minutes to ascend to the tortoise step, keeping the balance and trembling their steps in order not to slip and fall by the cliff.
